WEBVTT

00:05.339 --> 00:07.041
[Catherine] <i>Previously</i>
<i>on</i> The Spanish Princess...

00:07.074 --> 00:09.243
[Henry] My sister Mary is now
dowager Queen of France.

00:09.276 --> 00:13.013
So now I must arrange another marriage
that cements our Anglo-French alliance.

00:13.047 --> 00:14.582
What does my brother say
my fate should be?

00:14.615 --> 00:16.117
[Catherine]
<i>Henry, your sister writes to me.</i>

00:16.150 --> 00:17.518
She has married Charlie Brandon.

00:17.551 --> 00:18.786
Damn them both to hell!

00:19.019 --> 00:20.454
[Maggie]
<i>What does God want from us?</i>

00:20.488 --> 00:23.391
Perhaps He tests us through temptation.

00:23.424 --> 00:24.558
[Meg]
<i>Where is Angus?</i>

00:24.592 --> 00:27.528
He has had Jane Stewart
in his bed there since you left.

00:27.561 --> 00:30.598
Get out, and do not come back.

00:30.631 --> 00:33.100
I'm your husband, so all of this is mine.

00:33.134 --> 00:34.668
[Maggie]
Princess Mary wants her mother.

00:34.702 --> 00:35.770
She is strong.

00:35.803 --> 00:36.804
[Catherine]
<i>She is not a boy.</i>

00:37.037 --> 00:38.372
[Henry]
<i>I'm told you are carrying a child.</i>

00:38.406 --> 00:39.473
Is it mine?

00:39.507 --> 00:42.610
[screaming]

00:42.643 --> 00:43.644
[baby crying]

00:43.677 --> 00:45.446
[Catherine]
It is a boy.

00:45.479 --> 00:48.082
[Henry] I have a need
for something I cannot get.

00:48.115 --> 00:49.450
Give me a son.

00:52.253 --> 00:55.256
[dramatic music]

00:55.289 --> 00:58.259
♪ ♪

01:42.303 --> 01:45.272
[man and child playing]

01:53.581 --> 01:58.118
[laughter]

01:58.152 --> 02:00.287
[Elizabeth]
Yay!

02:00.321 --> 02:02.890
[laughs]

02:03.123 --> 02:06.126
♪ ♪

02:14.568 --> 02:17.571
[laughter, playing]

02:34.188 --> 02:35.923
[sighs]

02:36.156 --> 02:39.159
♪ ♪

02:48.903 --> 02:50.371
Ah!

03:00.214 --> 03:03.584
[Lina] Come away
from the window, Highness.

03:03.617 --> 03:04.919
You will catch a chill.

03:06.253 --> 03:08.756
-[Henry] Take him to his mother.
-[woman] Yes, Your Majesty.

03:17.398 --> 03:18.399
Your Grace.

03:21.335 --> 03:24.638
Cardinal Wolsey has been speaking
with your daughter.

03:24.672 --> 03:26.674
He says she is to marry.

03:30.711 --> 03:33.714
♪ ♪

03:46.927 --> 03:48.629
[man]
Your Grace.

03:51.966 --> 03:53.534
Henry...

03:54.468 --> 03:56.503
...I am told that Wolsey
now fancies himself

03:56.537 --> 03:57.838
of higher office than the queen,

03:57.871 --> 04:00.507
as he informs my daughter
that she shall be wed.

04:00.541 --> 04:02.476
The only way to rebuild
my alliance with the French--

04:02.509 --> 04:05.479
since my sister threw herself
away on Charlie Brandon--

04:05.512 --> 04:07.381
is to wed our daughter to their dauphin.

04:07.414 --> 04:08.549
It isn't only Wolsey.

04:08.582 --> 04:12.620
The Earl of Wiltshire also calls for it,
and he's ambassador to France.

04:12.653 --> 04:14.455
Why would you object?

04:14.488 --> 04:15.956
You've never shown interest
in the girl before.

04:15.990 --> 04:17.558
I am her mother.

04:17.591 --> 04:18.659
And Queen.

04:18.692 --> 04:22.429
Meanwhile, I must suffer my sister Mary
and Charles Brandon out in France

04:22.463 --> 04:25.366
and be forced to feign that I don't want
her head upon a spike.

04:25.399 --> 04:28.002
Thank goodness you're obedient.

04:28.035 --> 04:29.703
No one else is.

04:34.008 --> 04:37.011
[dramatic music]

04:37.044 --> 04:38.879
♪ ♪

04:38.912 --> 04:41.482
[Catherine]
<i>To my dearest nephew Charles...</i>

04:41.515 --> 04:44.551
<i>we hear great stories</i>
<i>of your kingship in Spain</i>

04:44.585 --> 04:47.955
<i>since my father Ferdinand's passing,</i>

04:47.988 --> 04:51.025
<i>and I write in hope</i>
<i>that I may see you soon in person.</i>

04:52.359 --> 04:54.495
<i>There is a meeting planned</i>
<i>between my husband</i>

04:54.528 --> 04:56.664
<i>and the French in Calais.</i>

04:56.697 --> 04:58.499
<i>Henry seeks a new alliance</i>

04:58.532 --> 05:00.934
<i>sealed with the betrothal</i>
<i>of our daughter Princess Mary</i>

05:00.968 --> 05:02.736
<i>to the French dauphin.</i>

05:03.570 --> 05:06.040
<i>But I wonder if there is</i>
<i>a far more valuable alliance</i>

05:06.073 --> 05:08.042
<i>to be made instead...</i>

05:08.075 --> 05:10.844
<i>with you, the King of Spain,</i>

05:10.878 --> 05:12.813
<i>as you surely need a wife yourself,</i>

05:12.846 --> 05:15.549
<i>and who could be more fitting</i>
<i>than my daughter?</i>

05:21.355 --> 05:23.891
I will take it
to the Spanish Ambassador, Highness.

05:25.592 --> 05:26.727
Lina?

05:28.595 --> 05:32.566
You will remain here with your husband
when we sail to France.

05:34.401 --> 05:35.736
You cannot travel now.

05:37.538 --> 05:38.906
Take care of him.

05:42.376 --> 05:44.511
Thank you, Catherine.

05:45.746 --> 05:48.749
♪ ♪

05:52.820 --> 05:55.823
[indistinct chatter]

06:04.665 --> 06:05.766
Thomas.

06:07.601 --> 06:10.637
-It is good to see you again.
-And you, Maggie.

06:10.671 --> 06:13.140
[John]
Put all that back on the ship!

06:13.373 --> 06:15.743
We don't need what you got!

06:15.776 --> 06:17.111
[More] There has been
some small disturbance

06:17.144 --> 06:20.380
over foreign tradesmen
arriving from Europe.

06:20.414 --> 06:22.149
We've doubled the number
of soldiers on the streets

06:22.382 --> 06:23.717
to ensure peace.

06:23.751 --> 06:25.119
My son is one of them.

06:25.152 --> 06:26.653
Oh, do not fear.

06:26.687 --> 06:28.088
It will all come to nothing.

06:28.122 --> 06:29.623
I hope not.

06:29.656 --> 06:30.991
He's seen enough fighting.

06:34.094 --> 06:36.830
Would you mind Princess Mary a moment?

06:36.864 --> 06:38.432
Of course.

06:42.970 --> 06:44.138
[Maggie]
Your Grace.

06:46.540 --> 06:50.144
Princess Mary has not yet been told
what's to happen to her

06:50.177 --> 06:51.612
when she is betrothed.

06:51.645 --> 06:53.847
I assumed you would want to tell her.

06:53.881 --> 06:56.950
We do not know yet
if she will be matched with France.

06:56.984 --> 07:01.088
Who an English princess marries
is not the province of a butcher's boy.

07:01.121 --> 07:03.423
Perhaps we'll find another suitor.

07:04.491 --> 07:07.194
[John]
Oi, we got our own cows, yeah?

07:07.427 --> 07:10.531
We don't need your poxy foreign shit!

07:10.564 --> 07:12.499
[Wiltshire]
Beg your Grace's pardon.

07:12.533 --> 07:14.902
The language of the docks is
too coarse for a lady's ears.

07:14.935 --> 07:16.170
[Henry]
He's right, though.

07:16.203 --> 07:17.805
Nothing beats English leather.

07:17.838 --> 07:20.140
Look at this saddle
Stafford had made me for me.

07:20.174 --> 07:21.775
This'll put Francis in his place.

07:21.809 --> 07:24.111
Ah, word is he's too drunk
to even sit in his.

07:24.144 --> 07:27.681
Ah, that does not bode well
for the good character of his son.

07:28.849 --> 07:31.552
I don't know what you're
so sour-faced about, Wolsey.

07:31.585 --> 07:33.921
I've just made you
Chancellor of England, haven't I?

07:35.956 --> 07:38.926
God knows I couldn't stand your whining.

07:38.959 --> 07:41.128
[Wolsey chuckles]

07:41.161 --> 07:44.164
♪ ♪

08:01.782 --> 08:04.685
The Duke of Albany will be gone
for just a few weeks.

08:04.718 --> 08:08.856
He's to visit your mean old Uncle Henry
and the King of France.

08:08.889 --> 08:10.524
They're having a great party.

08:10.557 --> 08:12.025
There'll be fountains running with wine,

08:12.059 --> 08:15.696
horses wearing jewels,
and a tree laden with sugar-plum pies.

08:15.729 --> 08:19.032
[chuckles] I think Hal Stewart
might be telling you fibs.

08:19.066 --> 08:20.968
I'm telling you, he's not.

08:21.001 --> 08:24.204
I will be ten times my size
when you see me next.

08:24.238 --> 08:26.206
-[Meg laughs]
-Hal Stewart will act

08:26.240 --> 08:28.542
as guardian to the princes till I'm back.

08:28.575 --> 08:30.077
He'll keep you safe.

08:31.578 --> 08:32.846
Come on.

08:38.685 --> 08:40.087
[Meg]
How did you get in here?

08:40.120 --> 08:42.022
Get out!

08:42.723 --> 08:45.893
You're my wife, Meg,
so I have a right to be here.

08:45.926 --> 08:49.663
Ah, so the minute that Albany is gone,
you sneak in like a thief in the night!

08:51.231 --> 08:52.766
So what happened?

08:52.799 --> 08:56.069
Your floozy finally saw sense
and threw you out?

08:56.103 --> 08:57.938
The queen has said
she doesn't want you here.

08:59.106 --> 09:01.642
-I am her husband.
-Barely.

09:01.675 --> 09:03.911
You could hardly consummate the marriage.

09:03.944 --> 09:07.748
It was all bad breath,
bad poetry, and disappointment.

09:08.548 --> 09:12.552
In the eyes of the law,
the Pope, and God Himself,

09:12.586 --> 09:13.921
she is my wife,

09:13.954 --> 09:16.556
and she belongs to me until she dies.

09:16.590 --> 09:18.158
Or you do.

09:18.191 --> 09:22.763
Because if you come anywhere near my bed
with that thing,

09:22.796 --> 09:24.564
one of us will surely die.

09:24.598 --> 09:27.968
You from a stabbing or me from laughter.

09:28.001 --> 09:30.771
Well, if I were you,
I wouldn't want to be here

09:30.804 --> 09:33.040
when a woman makes that kind of promise.

09:33.073 --> 09:36.076
[dramatic music]

09:36.109 --> 09:39.112
♪ ♪

09:45.986 --> 09:48.689
Hal, take Jamie and Alexander
back to the castle.

09:48.722 --> 09:51.158
James's other children will be safe here.

09:52.693 --> 09:56.263
I have business to attend to
with the Earl of Angus.

09:56.296 --> 09:59.733
And I need to write
a letter to my brother.

09:59.766 --> 10:01.635
[Angus]
You think he'll help you?

10:01.668 --> 10:04.371
He wouldn't even help us when we were
trapped in that cellar for three weeks.

10:04.604 --> 10:07.607
♪ ♪

10:22.656 --> 10:25.659
[rousing music]

10:25.692 --> 10:28.695
♪ ♪

10:43.410 --> 10:46.113
If Englishmen hear tales
of this extravagance

10:46.146 --> 10:47.681
when many struggle to find work--

10:47.714 --> 10:49.383
They would kneel
at the greatness of their king

10:49.416 --> 10:51.018
and be obedient.

10:51.051 --> 10:54.054
[dramatic music]

10:54.087 --> 10:57.090
♪ ♪

11:11.772 --> 11:13.206
[chuckles]

11:20.080 --> 11:22.382
Brother. Catherine.

11:23.917 --> 11:24.951
Mary.

11:26.086 --> 11:28.121
Oh, it warms my heart to see you.

11:29.289 --> 11:30.390
Your Grace.

11:35.228 --> 11:37.230
[Mary]
Will you not embrace me, brother?

11:37.264 --> 11:39.299
We have paid the fines you ask of us.

11:39.332 --> 11:41.935
We beg your good opinion.

11:44.104 --> 11:46.306
-Henry--
-You betrayed me.

11:47.007 --> 11:48.408
Be thankful you won't hang for treason.

11:51.144 --> 11:54.214
Now our daughter must be prepared
to meet King Francis.

12:01.121 --> 12:02.889
The king will come round.

12:03.957 --> 12:05.459
I will make sure of it.

12:08.195 --> 12:10.764
[Mary]
Her fate is all my doing, isn't it?

12:10.797 --> 12:12.732
Because I married Charlie,

12:12.766 --> 12:15.102
she must be
the sacrificial lamb for France.

12:15.969 --> 12:17.504
A Mary for a Mary.

12:18.738 --> 12:20.841
Not if I have any say in it.

12:20.874 --> 12:23.877
♪ ♪

12:43.163 --> 12:44.297
Mary.

12:46.500 --> 12:48.835
Greet your lady mother. She addresses you.

12:52.873 --> 12:54.975
Marriage is the duty of a princess.

12:55.008 --> 12:57.177
And I will be here to help you.

12:57.210 --> 13:00.147
I have told her
that it will not happen yet.

13:00.180 --> 13:03.416
It will be many years
before she lives in France.

13:03.450 --> 13:05.385
So you must not be afraid.

13:05.418 --> 13:07.554
I'm not afraid.

13:07.787 --> 13:11.158
[chuckles]

13:11.191 --> 13:12.192
Good.

13:13.560 --> 13:15.962
That's good, Mary.

13:17.330 --> 13:21.067
[Spanish Herald]
His Highness, Charles V, King of Spain!

13:21.101 --> 13:22.536
I must find Henry.

13:24.104 --> 13:26.139
[woman]
Come along, Mary.

13:26.173 --> 13:29.176
[fanfare playing]

13:32.445 --> 13:34.514
[Catherine]
You remember His Majesty,

13:34.548 --> 13:37.050
Charles V, my nephew.

13:38.151 --> 13:40.086
My lady aunt.

13:41.888 --> 13:44.591
-It has been too many years.
-Mm.

13:46.493 --> 13:49.062
Your Grace, King Henry.

13:50.897 --> 13:53.200
I wasn't expecting to see you here.

13:53.233 --> 13:56.236
Ah, well, it's a meeting
of great kings of Europe.

13:56.269 --> 13:59.072
It's a chance to see my lady aunt
and to meet with you.

13:59.105 --> 14:01.274
Hmm. Well, Ferdinand made many errors,

14:01.308 --> 14:02.576
which are left to you to right.

14:04.277 --> 14:07.347
I have heard many stories
of your prowess--

14:07.380 --> 14:10.917
when you beat the French
and won a great victory for England.

14:10.951 --> 14:12.452
A shame to let it go to waste,

14:12.485 --> 14:15.922
when an alliance between Spain
and England makes us strong.

14:20.260 --> 14:21.561
His name is Guerrero.

14:23.430 --> 14:25.398
"Warrior."

14:25.432 --> 14:27.033
He's yours.

14:27.067 --> 14:28.568
He's a token of our nations' friendship.

14:28.602 --> 14:30.870
Please.

14:30.904 --> 14:33.106
He is trained the way my mother's was--

14:33.139 --> 14:35.442
to kill a man with a single kick.

14:37.644 --> 14:39.646
[Henry]
Thank you.

14:39.879 --> 14:40.914
I accept your gift.

14:50.390 --> 14:52.959
[whispering]
Why do you call him "Majesty"?

14:54.961 --> 14:56.630
It is his favored title.

14:58.298 --> 15:00.600
[John]
<i>The king should protect us,</i>

15:00.634 --> 15:04.638
but Englishmen go hungry
while foreigners grow fat.

15:04.671 --> 15:05.905
King Henry--

15:05.939 --> 15:08.074
Ha! King Henry does nothing,

15:08.108 --> 15:10.577
'cause he's too busy feasting
off of golden plates

15:10.610 --> 15:13.546
-in France until he's sick.
-[crowd clamors]

15:13.580 --> 15:17.517
Foreigners take our work
and destroy our livelihoods

15:17.550 --> 15:19.552
with their cheap foreign wares.

15:19.586 --> 15:23.923
I call on Englishmen to cherish
and defend themselves.

15:23.957 --> 15:28.295
Let's hurt and grieve these aliens
for the common good.

15:28.328 --> 15:30.130
Let's drive 'em out!

15:30.163 --> 15:32.165
-Who's with me?
-[crowd cheers]

15:32.198 --> 15:34.100
Come. Come, let's go home.

15:34.134 --> 15:35.969
[Oviedo]
I know there is unrest, Lina.

15:36.002 --> 15:38.271
But Londoners have never been this way.

15:38.305 --> 15:40.440
Merchants cannot match
the price of foreign goods.

15:40.473 --> 15:42.542
Apprentices are out of work.

15:42.575 --> 15:46.179
Men whose children have an empty belly
will find common cause.

15:47.347 --> 15:49.015
What should we do?

15:49.049 --> 15:52.485
I'm appointed to the Royal Guard
to keep the peace.

15:52.519 --> 15:55.121
I will keep you safe.

15:55.155 --> 15:58.158
♪ ♪

16:11.671 --> 16:14.674
[fanfare plays]

16:14.708 --> 16:17.711
[drum beating]

16:17.744 --> 16:20.747
♪ ♪

16:26.586 --> 16:28.488
[Wolsey]
Ah, a magnificent sight--

16:28.521 --> 16:31.157
two kings meeting for the first time.

16:31.191 --> 16:34.194
♪ ♪

16:41.234 --> 16:44.037
[music stops]

16:44.070 --> 16:45.705
Brother France.

16:45.739 --> 16:48.274
Brother England.

16:48.308 --> 16:50.243
Although, I hear that we are triplets,

16:50.276 --> 16:54.080
and Brother Spain is also at our party.

16:55.148 --> 16:56.716
Well...

16:56.750 --> 16:59.219
a little healthy competition
never hurt a powerful man.

17:01.454 --> 17:04.457
[warm music]

17:04.491 --> 17:07.494
♪ ♪

17:18.271 --> 17:21.174
I hear the dauphin
is a most handsome infant.

17:21.207 --> 17:24.244
Then why hasn't Francis brought him
to the summit?

17:24.277 --> 17:26.045
Perhaps he is sickly.

17:26.079 --> 17:27.580
Indeed, we know that newborn boys

17:27.614 --> 17:30.216
-are often weaker than girls.
-Hmm.

17:30.250 --> 17:32.051
He'll need to be strong
if he's to wed my daughter.

17:32.085 --> 17:35.221
The strongest choice
would be King Charles of Spain.

17:35.255 --> 17:38.358
20 years old and all the riches
of the New World at his feet.

17:38.391 --> 17:41.094
[fanfare plays]

17:41.127 --> 17:44.431
The Princess Mary of England.

17:54.073 --> 17:55.742
[whispering]
All shall be well.

18:02.715 --> 18:06.453
Handsome girl, though stubborn as a mule.

18:06.486 --> 18:08.421
[whispering]
Better that than a dull object

18:08.455 --> 18:09.689
-with an empty head.
-[chuckles]

18:09.722 --> 18:11.291
Then we'll make terms.

18:11.324 --> 18:12.659
No.

18:12.692 --> 18:14.727
We will see the dauphin first--

18:14.761 --> 18:17.163
She is pale, though. How is her health?

18:17.864 --> 18:18.865
She's sturdy.

18:20.767 --> 18:22.302
For her marriage portion,

18:22.335 --> 18:25.305
the girl would come
with substantial lands and properties.

18:25.338 --> 18:27.841
It is the dauphin's health
we would like to know about.

18:27.874 --> 18:31.110
My son could eat your stallion
in a single meal.

18:31.144 --> 18:32.312
Ha.

18:32.345 --> 18:35.548
There is no doubt about his strength.

18:35.582 --> 18:38.818
This is the figure we require
for Mary's dowry.

18:38.852 --> 18:40.520
In gold ducats.

18:43.122 --> 18:44.858
[Henry scoffs]

18:44.891 --> 18:47.327
You are surely jesting.

18:47.360 --> 18:50.630
Your father, Louis, was paid
barely half that to marry my sister.

18:50.663 --> 18:53.766
Your sister was a true princess.

18:54.534 --> 18:55.802
So is Mary.

18:57.136 --> 19:00.340
Your wife was married
to your brother, was she not?

19:00.373 --> 19:03.510
The Pope was asked
if you could even marry--

19:03.543 --> 19:07.547
if it could be lawful in the eyes of God.

19:09.215 --> 19:11.784
[dramatic music]

19:11.818 --> 19:13.486
♪ ♪

19:13.520 --> 19:15.255
Your Grace.

19:16.789 --> 19:19.259
How dare you insult the Queen of England?

19:19.292 --> 19:22.295
♪ ♪

19:22.328 --> 19:23.863
Come outside.

19:23.897 --> 19:26.933
[speaking French]

19:27.166 --> 19:28.635
I will gladly do so.

19:31.237 --> 19:32.639
Your Grace.

19:32.672 --> 19:34.841
♪ ♪

19:36.543 --> 19:37.777
[Maggie]
It will all be over soon,

19:37.810 --> 19:40.213
and then we will sail home, I promise.

19:40.246 --> 19:42.715
♪ ♪

19:46.352 --> 19:49.355
[applause]

19:59.332 --> 20:02.335
[crowd chattering]

20:12.478 --> 20:13.580
Ow.

20:14.547 --> 20:16.282
[exhales sharply]

20:16.316 --> 20:17.850
[Henry]
Ha!

20:19.352 --> 20:22.355
[cheering]

20:25.792 --> 20:28.494
[Francis]
Do you yield?

20:31.798 --> 20:32.799
Huh?

20:33.900 --> 20:37.470
I said, "Do you yield?"

20:38.605 --> 20:39.806
I yield!

20:39.839 --> 20:41.774
-[Francis chuckles]
-[Henry exhales sharply]

20:41.808 --> 20:44.410
[applause]

20:44.444 --> 20:47.380
[booing]

20:47.413 --> 20:49.882
[Francis laughs]

20:49.916 --> 20:51.618
Whoo!

20:51.651 --> 20:55.955
Bravely fought, Brother England.

20:55.989 --> 20:58.524
[spits]

20:58.558 --> 21:01.561
♪ ♪

21:04.764 --> 21:07.567
You're lucky I don't run you through.

21:07.600 --> 21:09.769
[Francis speaking French]

21:09.802 --> 21:11.904
-Henry--
-He maligned the legitimacy

21:11.938 --> 21:14.507
of our daughter
and the validity of our marriage.

21:14.540 --> 21:17.810
Mary has the purest bloodline
of all Europe.

21:17.844 --> 21:21.314
And this lecher thinks
he can haggle over her

21:21.347 --> 21:23.016
like so much horseflesh?

21:27.687 --> 21:30.690
[laughter outside]

21:32.859 --> 21:35.862
♪ ♪

21:37.864 --> 21:39.766
[man]
This ain't your home.

21:39.799 --> 21:41.768
[men laughing]

21:41.801 --> 21:44.070
[indistinct shouting]

21:44.303 --> 21:46.339
[Lina]
We are being threatened.

21:46.372 --> 21:49.709
A gallows drawn in pig's blood.

21:49.742 --> 21:51.511
Was it them?

21:51.544 --> 21:53.413
I don't--

21:55.448 --> 21:56.983
Go inside.

21:57.016 --> 22:00.019
♪ ♪

22:05.591 --> 22:07.827
Curfews have been put in place.

22:08.528 --> 22:12.699
I am on duty, on patrol.

22:12.732 --> 22:15.101
You will not be here at night?

22:15.334 --> 22:17.003
We will be here alone?

22:17.036 --> 22:19.405
None shall come to any harm.

22:20.740 --> 22:23.743
♪ ♪

22:29.916 --> 22:31.417
[Rosa]
Catherine?

22:32.518 --> 22:35.488
Highness!
[laughing]

22:35.521 --> 22:36.789
Rosa!

22:37.724 --> 22:41.360
It is so wonderful to see you again.

22:48.000 --> 22:49.936
I can't believe it's really you.

22:51.003 --> 22:52.572
How are you here?

22:52.605 --> 22:54.574
We are with the Spanish court.

22:54.607 --> 22:56.442
My husband is a navigator.

22:57.543 --> 22:59.846
You didn't get my letters?

22:59.879 --> 23:00.947
I...

23:02.749 --> 23:04.917
I didn't read them all.

23:04.951 --> 23:06.919
It was--
[sniffles]

23:06.953 --> 23:08.821
It has been painful.

23:10.757 --> 23:12.558
I know.

23:12.592 --> 23:13.793
I'm sorry.

23:15.161 --> 23:16.796
Lina wrote to me.

23:18.097 --> 23:20.600
But now you have a daughter.

23:20.633 --> 23:24.103
Mine are Magdalena, Cristina, and Lucia.

23:24.137 --> 23:25.605
[chuckles]

23:26.773 --> 23:28.941
Where is Princess Mary?

23:28.975 --> 23:30.676
I've longed to meet her.

23:30.710 --> 23:34.113
Ah, she is with Lady Pole.

23:34.147 --> 23:37.583
Wolsey seeks to wed her to the dauphin.

23:37.617 --> 23:41.154
I would sooner see her married to Charles,
the King of Spain.

23:43.756 --> 23:46.559
But she's only six years old.

23:51.130 --> 23:53.833
How is Lina? Is she here?

23:54.834 --> 23:56.636
No. She is with child again.

23:56.669 --> 23:57.904
[chuckles]

23:57.937 --> 23:59.672
She has two boys already.

24:00.506 --> 24:02.642
I'm sorry, Rosa.

24:02.675 --> 24:04.443
I must go.

24:05.711 --> 24:07.547
May we speak more later?

24:08.915 --> 24:10.082
Yes, dear Catherine.

24:11.184 --> 24:13.152
We must speak further.

24:13.186 --> 24:14.821
We must.

24:14.854 --> 24:17.857
♪ ♪

24:19.192 --> 24:20.560
[child]
Mama!

24:20.593 --> 24:22.028
[gasps]
Hello.

24:24.530 --> 24:28.167
[man speaking Spanish]

24:28.201 --> 24:30.169
[Rosa speaks Spanish]

24:30.203 --> 24:33.206
♪ ♪

24:50.022 --> 24:51.891
[Catherine]
Henry.

24:54.760 --> 24:56.229
Let me see.

24:58.564 --> 25:00.566
[sighs]

25:03.236 --> 25:05.571
We cannot wed Mary to his son.

25:07.240 --> 25:09.175
He insulted both of us.

25:09.208 --> 25:10.977
We must consider Charles for her.

25:11.010 --> 25:13.045
I have defended your honor, Catherine.

25:13.946 --> 25:15.948
Be satisfied with that.

25:22.088 --> 25:24.190
[scoffs, sniffles]

25:24.223 --> 25:26.659
Ah, your sister Mary
seems lit up with happiness

25:26.692 --> 25:28.094
at her husband, Charlie.

25:29.528 --> 25:31.664
They are blessed as we are.

25:35.268 --> 25:37.737
Look at what God has given us.

25:38.671 --> 25:40.106
This kingdom...

25:42.108 --> 25:43.609
...and each other.

25:45.077 --> 25:47.613
So few ever know this happiness.

25:52.184 --> 25:53.953
Perhaps it is enough.

25:58.224 --> 26:00.159
Perhaps God means for it to be enough.

26:00.192 --> 26:01.294
Enough?

26:02.561 --> 26:04.664
You mean without a son?

26:07.800 --> 26:11.737
Why grant me all this power and fortune...

26:13.339 --> 26:15.141
...if not to build a dynasty?

26:16.742 --> 26:20.079
God tests me more than others
because I am the king.

26:21.814 --> 26:23.316
And I shall pass His test.

26:25.918 --> 26:28.754
I've received a letter from Meg.

26:28.788 --> 26:31.791
♪ ♪

26:37.697 --> 26:38.965
[Meg]
<i>Dear brother...</i>

26:40.866 --> 26:42.969
<i>...I have sad news to share.</i>

26:43.002 --> 26:44.770
[snores]

26:44.804 --> 26:48.074
[Meg]
<i>I think that I've lost my mind.</i>

26:48.107 --> 26:49.375
[laughing]

26:49.608 --> 26:51.711
<i>I fear this malady has</i>
<i>afflicted me a long time...</i>

26:51.744 --> 26:53.045
[screaming]

26:53.079 --> 26:54.313
<i>...since before I married Angus.</i>

26:54.347 --> 26:55.715
[laughing]

26:55.748 --> 26:59.185
<i>Indeed, I believe it is the cause</i>
<i>of that unfortunate match.</i>

26:59.218 --> 27:02.221
♪ ♪

27:05.725 --> 27:06.926
<i>Since the law tells us</i>

27:06.959 --> 27:08.627
<i>that a marriage cannot be considered valid</i>

27:08.661 --> 27:11.197
<i>if one party was insane at the time,</i>

27:11.230 --> 27:15.768
<i>my marriage should be annulled</i>
<i>as soon as possible.</i>

27:15.801 --> 27:18.237
<i>Please write to the Pope</i>
<i>and bid him do so swiftly.</i>

27:18.270 --> 27:19.372
[scoffs]

27:19.405 --> 27:22.675
She cannot just discard a man
whom God has joined her to.

27:22.708 --> 27:25.845
[Henry]
We must attend the entertainment.

27:25.878 --> 27:28.881
♪ ♪

27:28.914 --> 27:30.916
[Catherine sighs]

27:32.651 --> 27:35.187
[tapping on table]

27:35.221 --> 27:38.224
♪ ♪

27:44.096 --> 27:47.733
"Hence, heart, with her that must depart."

27:49.101 --> 27:52.872
"And hald thee with thy sovereign.

27:52.905 --> 27:55.274
"For I had never want nae heart,

27:55.307 --> 27:58.310
nor have the heart that does me pain..."

27:58.344 --> 27:59.712
What are you doing?

27:59.745 --> 28:01.414
Everything in this house belongs to me...

28:01.447 --> 28:02.882
No, you will not touch a single thing.

28:02.915 --> 28:04.116
...and I shall take it.

28:04.150 --> 28:07.019
You'll find in law that it is mine.

28:07.053 --> 28:08.454
You can't do that.

28:08.687 --> 28:10.089
Oh, I can...

28:10.122 --> 28:11.257
[Meg]
Angus!

28:12.124 --> 28:13.125
...and will.

28:13.159 --> 28:16.162
♪ ♪

28:23.035 --> 28:26.038
[light music playing]

28:26.072 --> 28:28.841
[indistinct chatter]

28:35.347 --> 28:37.917
[Henry] What does he say to them?
Does he speak against me?

28:37.950 --> 28:39.819
No.

28:39.852 --> 28:41.921
No, he misses you.

28:41.954 --> 28:44.323
He hopes to be your friend again.

28:44.356 --> 28:46.859
Well, he shouldn't have lied to me.

28:46.892 --> 28:50.096
He said that he was true, and he was not.

28:50.129 --> 28:52.364
In truth, I blame Mary more.

28:52.398 --> 28:54.300
Men are weak,

28:54.333 --> 28:56.102
easily beguiled.

28:56.135 --> 28:59.138
♪ ♪

29:05.811 --> 29:06.979
[Catherine]
Albany.

29:08.447 --> 29:11.784
I would have you speak
with Henry's sister Meg.

29:11.817 --> 29:13.986
I know that she is unhappy up in Scotland,

29:14.019 --> 29:17.056
but there is nothing that the king can do,
and she must make the best of it.

29:17.089 --> 29:18.924
I don't agree.

29:18.958 --> 29:21.227
I think if you're unhappy,
you should change it.

29:21.260 --> 29:23.829
I took my destiny in my own hands,

29:23.863 --> 29:26.298
and I am blessed now with a joy
that I had never known before.

29:26.332 --> 29:28.100
You were free to marry.

29:28.134 --> 29:30.336
But Meg has made her choice,
and she must abide by it.

29:30.369 --> 29:32.138
Mary, my darling,
we should listen to the queen.

29:32.171 --> 29:33.806
Meg has consulted law books

29:33.839 --> 29:35.374
and learned there may be grounds
for an annulment.

29:35.407 --> 29:36.509
There are not.

29:37.776 --> 29:41.113
And the Douglases are useful to the king
because they are pro-English,

29:41.147 --> 29:44.850
so he cannot make a stand against them
in some harebrained quest against Angus.

29:46.218 --> 29:48.187
Please ensure she knows this.

29:52.124 --> 29:54.126
[sighs]

29:55.528 --> 29:56.562
[exhales sharply]

29:56.795 --> 29:58.164
[clamoring outside]

29:58.197 --> 30:00.966
-[door opens, closes]
-Lina, quickly, bring the boys.

30:01.000 --> 30:02.334
-What is it?
-The curfews have been broken.

30:02.368 --> 30:04.203
I will take you to the palace
where it is safe.

30:04.236 --> 30:06.205
-[Oviedo] Come on. Come on.
-[clamoring continues]

30:06.238 --> 30:08.340
[speaking Spanish]
Come on, come on.

30:08.374 --> 30:09.441
Move away.

30:09.475 --> 30:11.110
[man]
All right, lads, let's have it.

30:11.143 --> 30:12.378
[soldier]
Drop that club!

30:14.180 --> 30:16.048
[Oviedo]
Come on. Come with me.

30:16.081 --> 30:18.884
[speaking Spanish]

30:18.918 --> 30:21.921
[dramatic music]

30:22.988 --> 30:24.456
-[horse whinnies]
-[man] Get back here!

30:24.490 --> 30:27.193
By order of the king!

30:27.226 --> 30:29.461
Bessie's house is closer than the palace.

30:29.495 --> 30:31.063
There will be guards there for her son.

30:31.096 --> 30:33.299
[Oviedo speaking Spanish]
Let's go, come with me.

30:33.332 --> 30:34.833
Next to me! Next to me!

30:36.936 --> 30:39.205
[Rosa]
My dear Catherine,

30:39.238 --> 30:41.540
such pain.

30:41.574 --> 30:43.842
I see that plainly.

30:43.876 --> 30:46.111
[light music playing]

30:46.145 --> 30:48.948
Henry has a healthy boy

30:48.981 --> 30:50.916
with my own lady, Bessie.

30:50.950 --> 30:53.552
♪ ♪

30:53.586 --> 30:55.621
All my efforts have been in vain.

30:57.156 --> 30:58.424
I am sorry.

31:00.025 --> 31:01.393
But...

31:01.427 --> 31:03.095
he is still kind to you?

31:03.128 --> 31:04.263
The king?

31:05.264 --> 31:07.066
He has...

31:07.099 --> 31:08.500
changed.

31:11.437 --> 31:13.272
He is disappointed.

31:13.305 --> 31:15.107
It is not his fault.

31:15.140 --> 31:16.508
I have given him nothing.

31:16.542 --> 31:18.277
No.

31:18.310 --> 31:20.613
Forgive me, but this is not true.

31:21.647 --> 31:24.416
And you hurt your own heart without cause.

31:25.284 --> 31:28.954
You have given the king
a strong, intelligent daughter.

31:28.988 --> 31:31.090
-What use is that?
-Catherine.

31:31.123 --> 31:33.459
Your mother is Queen Isabella of Castile.

31:34.593 --> 31:37.963
Your daughter is from a line
of warrior queens.

31:39.231 --> 31:42.234
Forget about some milksop English boy.

31:44.103 --> 31:48.274
Mary is your heir, your legacy.

31:48.307 --> 31:51.644
She will be the one to rule
and follow you in greatness.

31:52.978 --> 31:55.281
But she needs her mother's love
to do that.

32:01.253 --> 32:03.355
I did not expect to see him.

32:04.356 --> 32:05.991
What happened to his eye?

32:06.025 --> 32:08.327
-He lost it in a joust.
-Oh.

32:09.461 --> 32:12.131
I should've told you he was here.

32:12.164 --> 32:13.432
I'm sorry.

32:17.236 --> 32:18.470
Rosa.

32:18.504 --> 32:21.674
[music stops, applause]

32:23.509 --> 32:24.543
You look well.

32:26.412 --> 32:28.447
You look beautiful.

32:28.480 --> 32:29.515
Like a...

32:31.250 --> 32:32.351
...peach.

32:32.384 --> 32:33.619
No. A--

32:33.652 --> 32:36.555
-[Rosa laughs]
-Sorry. [chuckles]

32:36.588 --> 32:39.658
I am well. Thank you.

32:39.692 --> 32:41.360
Are you happy?

32:42.461 --> 32:45.030
More than I ever thought
it possible to be.

32:46.131 --> 32:48.367
I think about you so often.

32:49.968 --> 32:52.071
What might have been.

32:56.108 --> 32:57.710
You should not regret.

32:59.011 --> 33:01.213
Our choices take us
where we're meant to be.

33:01.246 --> 33:03.649
[footsteps approaching]

33:05.084 --> 33:09.221
[exhales deeply]
My husband, Alvaro.

33:12.024 --> 33:14.059
I hope you may find peace, Edward.

33:15.094 --> 33:18.063
[light music playing]

33:18.097 --> 33:20.599
♪ ♪

33:20.632 --> 33:22.701
-Ah--
-Oh, for the love of God, Wolsey,

33:22.735 --> 33:24.136
get away from me.

33:24.169 --> 33:26.472
[Charles]
Ah.

33:26.505 --> 33:30.075
The man they call the "Alter Rex."

33:31.410 --> 33:33.545
[Wolsey]
Uh, you are mistaken.

33:33.579 --> 33:37.015
No... no one calls me that.

33:37.049 --> 33:38.650
[Charles]
Yes, I have heard it.

33:38.684 --> 33:41.220
The "other king."

33:42.588 --> 33:45.057
Well, uh, that is what is said.

33:45.090 --> 33:46.759
[Henry chuckles]

33:46.792 --> 33:48.260
It's very droll.

33:49.194 --> 33:52.164
[dramatic music]

33:52.197 --> 33:55.200
♪ ♪

33:56.168 --> 33:59.438
It's like a play written
for "Twelfth Night,"

33:59.471 --> 34:03.041
where-where a stupid mummer

34:03.075 --> 34:05.110
thinks he should be king.

34:06.578 --> 34:08.614
[laughs]

34:08.647 --> 34:11.417
♪ ♪

34:37.543 --> 34:39.611
[Bessie]
Lina. Oviedo. Come in. Come in.

34:39.645 --> 34:41.713
I'm sorry to bother you
in the middle of the night.

34:42.448 --> 34:44.149
[Bessie]
<i>Are you all safe?</i>

34:44.183 --> 34:46.585
We heard the fights break out.
You must've been afraid.

34:46.618 --> 34:48.153
[Oviedo]
We will not burden you for long.

34:48.187 --> 34:50.355
[Bessie] I suppose it was bound
to happen sooner or later.

34:50.389 --> 34:53.859
When men are starving and out of work,
unrest will surely follow.

34:54.092 --> 34:55.561
Not in England.

34:55.594 --> 34:59.298
It is not the way of honest working men
who know God's order.

34:59.331 --> 35:02.134
It's the incomers who have done this.

35:02.167 --> 35:05.671
Incomers are the victims of the violence.

35:06.505 --> 35:09.274
[scoffs] Well, they take
the work of the Englishmen,

35:09.308 --> 35:11.109
and this is what results.

35:11.143 --> 35:13.512
The Tudors do not brook rebellion.

35:13.545 --> 35:17.316
Some heads on Tower Bridge will soon
remind people of the proper order here.

35:17.349 --> 35:18.684
[chuckles]

35:22.688 --> 35:24.890
I must go to assist the Sheriff's men.

35:25.123 --> 35:28.126
♪ ♪

35:30.362 --> 35:31.830
Lina.

35:33.198 --> 35:36.502
[door opens, closes]

35:36.535 --> 35:41.206
[man]
The king calls us to leave for England!

35:41.240 --> 35:42.641
[Brandon]
Your Grace.

35:43.709 --> 35:47.546
I heard about the rioting in London
and that you must return immediately.

35:48.680 --> 35:52.551
Maybe I should raise the price of ale.
That might stop them.

35:53.652 --> 35:57.356
Not all young men can drink
like we used to, eh, Charlie?

35:58.557 --> 36:00.292
Still be up at dawn to hunt.

36:01.927 --> 36:04.196
[chuckles]

36:04.229 --> 36:05.564
Those were the days.

36:12.204 --> 36:14.540
I'm told that you paid your fines.

36:14.573 --> 36:17.576
♪ ♪

36:17.609 --> 36:19.778
Mm.

36:19.811 --> 36:20.946
You are pardoned.

36:22.347 --> 36:25.384
You may return to England with us,
you and Mary, if you wish.

36:25.417 --> 36:27.352
Thank you, Henry.

36:27.386 --> 36:29.488
God bless you.

36:29.521 --> 36:32.291
♪ ♪

36:36.895 --> 36:38.397
[Maggie]
Catherine.

36:38.430 --> 36:40.432
Princess Mary is ready to leave.

36:41.533 --> 36:42.868
What has he decided?

36:42.901 --> 36:44.903
Who will she marry?

36:44.937 --> 36:48.540
He is weighing up the merits
of the dauphin, my nephew Charles...

36:49.708 --> 36:52.578
...or if he trusts me or Wolsey more.

36:52.611 --> 36:55.213
♪ ♪

36:55.247 --> 36:56.448
[Rosa]
Catherine.

36:57.583 --> 37:00.218
Highness, you are leaving?

37:00.953 --> 37:02.454
[sniffles]

37:02.487 --> 37:06.558
It was wonderful to see you, Rosa,
and so happy.

37:06.592 --> 37:08.794
You deserve it all.

37:10.796 --> 37:14.933
The secret to happiness
is to value what you have,

37:14.967 --> 37:17.269
not yearn for what you do not.

37:17.302 --> 37:20.272
[soft music]

37:20.305 --> 37:23.308
♪ ♪

37:23.342 --> 37:25.811
Love your daughter...

37:25.844 --> 37:27.479
and your God.

37:28.313 --> 37:30.349
Hold on to them.

37:30.382 --> 37:32.017
They are what matter.

37:32.250 --> 37:33.819
They are what will endure.

37:35.320 --> 37:38.323
♪ ♪

37:39.424 --> 37:41.293
[Catherine laughs]

37:41.326 --> 37:43.562
I want you to have this.

37:44.429 --> 37:46.531
You need it more than I do now.

37:46.565 --> 37:49.568
♪ ♪

37:52.404 --> 37:54.640
Find your way back to her...

37:54.673 --> 37:58.010
to your daughter and to yourself.

37:59.978 --> 38:01.980
[sniffles]

38:03.682 --> 38:04.950
[exhales sharply]

38:07.786 --> 38:08.854
[sighs]

38:10.622 --> 38:13.625
♪ ♪

38:32.444 --> 38:34.846
[indistinct chatter]

38:34.880 --> 38:36.515
Mary?

38:37.582 --> 38:39.017
Come sit with me.

38:39.051 --> 38:40.886
Let's watch the waves.

38:44.956 --> 38:46.925
[man laughs]

38:46.958 --> 38:49.961
[chatter continues]

38:52.964 --> 38:56.635
[laughter]

38:56.668 --> 38:59.671
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

39:03.575 --> 39:06.011
Henry, I would like to educate
our daughter.

39:06.044 --> 39:07.546
Educate her?

39:07.579 --> 39:10.082
Not just in needlework and music...

39:10.115 --> 39:14.419
but philosophy, languages,
affairs of state.

39:15.420 --> 39:18.590
She will be educated as a boy would be,
and I will oversee it.

39:18.623 --> 39:20.559
For what reason?

39:21.660 --> 39:23.862
She will be a queen one day

39:23.895 --> 39:25.764
and must learn how to rule.

39:27.499 --> 39:31.369
Once her betrothal is decided,
you may teach the girl anything you wish.

39:33.505 --> 39:34.940
Thank you, Henry.

39:36.408 --> 39:37.743
You are a good man.

39:43.715 --> 39:44.716
[laughter]

39:44.750 --> 39:46.384
[Mary]
Pretty girl.

39:46.418 --> 39:47.586
[laughter]

39:47.619 --> 39:49.621
[Mary Brandon]
Oh, Mary, that's wonderful.

39:50.789 --> 39:53.024
What causes so much merriment?

39:53.058 --> 39:56.528
Mary is an uncanny mimic of King Francis.

39:58.830 --> 40:00.799
May I hear it, Mary?

40:14.646 --> 40:17.115
Reggie was the same with me.

40:17.149 --> 40:20.852
He was away for so long,
he did not know a mother's love.

40:20.886 --> 40:22.988
He would not speak to me either.

40:24.990 --> 40:29.427
But it is not too late
if you work hard with her.

40:30.095 --> 40:32.664
-She just needs time.
-I will give it to her.

40:34.032 --> 40:35.967
I will be worthy of her.

40:37.969 --> 40:41.973
Your Grace, we will reach England
by nightfall.

40:43.675 --> 40:46.444
Thank you, Lord Stafford.

40:50.849 --> 40:53.852
[dramatic music]

40:53.885 --> 40:56.888
♪ ♪

41:00.458 --> 41:04.029
[people shouting]

41:04.062 --> 41:07.065
[people clamoring]

41:09.568 --> 41:11.036
[Oviedo]
Enough of this!

41:11.069 --> 41:12.504
Enough.

41:14.005 --> 41:15.073
Go home.

41:15.106 --> 41:18.109
♪ ♪

41:19.878 --> 41:22.848
Do not draw your arms at me.

41:22.881 --> 41:25.584
Go home, and there will be no charge.

41:26.885 --> 41:27.919
[Henry Pole]
Arrest them!

41:27.953 --> 41:30.755
I want all these men in chains!

41:30.789 --> 41:32.123
Kill the dogs!

41:32.157 --> 41:33.892
They dare to go against the king.

41:33.925 --> 41:35.861
Kill them all!

41:35.894 --> 41:36.895
[horse whinnies]

41:36.928 --> 41:38.763
Henry, no! He's unarmed!

41:38.797 --> 41:40.999
[man gurgles, grunts]

41:41.032 --> 41:44.035
[people clamoring]

41:44.069 --> 41:47.072
♪ ♪

41:50.108 --> 41:51.109
[Bessie]
Lina.

41:52.744 --> 41:54.079
[Oviedo]
He's gone.

42:00.518 --> 42:02.087
[Lina] We are not safe here.
We should go to the palace.

42:02.120 --> 42:03.288
[door closes]

42:03.521 --> 42:06.524
♪ ♪

42:06.558 --> 42:08.159
I tried to stop them.

42:08.193 --> 42:09.728
I saw it.

42:09.761 --> 42:11.263
I saw what Henry Pole did.

42:11.296 --> 42:14.566
[Bessie] They rise against the king,
they get whatever fate his men decide.

42:14.599 --> 42:17.602
♪ ♪

42:18.303 --> 42:20.772
You are not the same as Pole.

42:20.805 --> 42:22.707
You must not think you are.

42:24.109 --> 42:27.078
I see the rioters and the immigrants...

42:27.112 --> 42:31.116
poor men alike,
but they fight and blame each other.

42:33.251 --> 42:36.054
When, in truth, it is the king
who is the cause

42:36.087 --> 42:37.722
of all their suffering,
with his endless taxes.

42:37.756 --> 42:39.190
Don't say such things.

42:40.058 --> 42:41.593
Not even to me.

42:41.626 --> 42:44.296
♪ ♪

42:53.672 --> 42:55.840
[man shouting]

42:55.874 --> 42:57.809
[people clamoring]

42:57.842 --> 42:59.311
[glass shattering]

42:59.344 --> 43:01.246
[Henry]
How do we get through?

43:03.014 --> 43:05.984
For the love of God, Stafford,
protect my daughter and the queen.

43:07.218 --> 43:10.221
[men grunting, shouting]

43:13.591 --> 43:15.226
[swords clash, man grunts]

43:15.260 --> 43:18.263
♪ ♪

43:23.301 --> 43:25.704
Mary, I'm just--

43:25.737 --> 43:27.605
Mary?

43:27.639 --> 43:30.308
No. Where-w-where is she?

43:30.342 --> 43:32.010
-Mary!
-Stay on your horse, Your Grace.

43:32.043 --> 43:33.211
I will find her.

43:33.244 --> 43:36.715
-[Catherine] Mary?
-Mary? Princess Mary?

43:36.748 --> 43:38.616
[grunting]

43:38.650 --> 43:40.952
Mary! Mary!

43:40.986 --> 43:43.722
-Ah. Mary!
-[woman screams]

43:43.755 --> 43:45.690
-Mary!
-[man screams]

43:45.724 --> 43:47.125
-[Catherine panting]
-[man shouts]

43:47.158 --> 43:49.027
Ah! Mary! Mary!

43:50.195 --> 43:51.796
Mary!

43:53.198 --> 43:55.166
Mary! Mary!

43:55.200 --> 43:56.835
Ah, ah!

43:56.868 --> 44:00.005
-Mary!
-[horse whinnies]

44:00.038 --> 44:02.674
Mary. Mary!

44:02.707 --> 44:05.076
Ah! Mary.

44:05.110 --> 44:07.112
[Henry]
Mary! Mary!

44:07.145 --> 44:09.748
[intense music]

44:09.781 --> 44:11.216
♪ ♪

44:11.249 --> 44:13.051
[girl]
Mother!

44:15.353 --> 44:17.088
Mary! Give her to me!

44:17.122 --> 44:18.690
Give-give her to me!

44:18.723 --> 44:20.759
Mary.

44:20.792 --> 44:23.795
♪ ♪

44:25.430 --> 44:28.433
[distant clamoring]

44:31.236 --> 44:32.904
[Henry]

44:35.240 --> 44:37.042
Stafford's found her!

44:37.075 --> 44:40.078
[dramatic music]

44:40.111 --> 44:43.114
♪ ♪

44:55.360 --> 44:56.895
Highness.

44:56.928 --> 44:58.163
Are you hurt?

44:58.196 --> 44:59.330
[Catherine sighs]

44:59.364 --> 45:01.266
We were caught in it.

45:01.299 --> 45:03.301
I lost Mary.

45:03.334 --> 45:05.103
I thought I was being punished.

45:06.438 --> 45:08.039
You-you and your child?

45:08.073 --> 45:09.340
We are well.

45:09.374 --> 45:10.875
The boys and Oviedo, too.

45:10.909 --> 45:12.911
-Good.
-But, Highness...

45:12.944 --> 45:15.146
[indistinct chatter]

45:15.180 --> 45:17.115
...some of the royal soldiers--

45:17.148 --> 45:18.783
Uh, take Mary.

45:18.817 --> 45:19.918
Henry.

45:20.885 --> 45:23.254
-I am worried for our daughter.
-The world's gone mad.

45:23.288 --> 45:25.056
First, treason in the city,

45:25.090 --> 45:28.960
and now my sister writes another letter
trying to shame me to all of Christendom.

45:31.196 --> 45:34.466
She even tries to resurrect
the dead Scots king.

45:35.934 --> 45:40.105
[Meg] <i>Dear brother,</i>
<i>I write to you in desperation.</i>

45:40.138 --> 45:42.874
<i>I have learned my husband, James IV,</i>

45:42.907 --> 45:47.145
<i>did not die at Flodden</i>
<i>but escaped and lives!</i>

45:47.178 --> 45:50.115
<i>This means my marriage</i>
<i>to the Earl of Angus is unlawful.</i>

45:50.148 --> 45:51.883
<i>I have checked this in the law books.</i>

45:51.916 --> 45:54.886
<i>Please appeal to the Pope on my behalf.</i>

45:54.919 --> 45:57.489
<i>He must annul my marriage.</i>

45:58.923 --> 46:01.926
[Catherine praying quietly, bell tolling]

46:05.797 --> 46:07.332
Bless me, Lord.

46:09.400 --> 46:11.002
I am a sinner.

46:13.037 --> 46:14.973
Grant me Your forgiveness,

46:15.006 --> 46:17.842
and help me know
what You would have me do.

46:19.410 --> 46:21.846
[praying quietly]

46:21.880 --> 46:24.883
♪ ♪

46:25.917 --> 46:28.553
[Catherine]
<i>To my dearest sister Meg,</i>

46:28.786 --> 46:32.157
<i>I bid you, please, desist your letters</i>

46:32.190 --> 46:35.026
<i>and this blasphemous assault on marriage.</i>

46:35.059 --> 46:39.931
<i>I have supported you and your regency</i>
<i>in every way I can.</i>

46:39.964 --> 46:43.468
<i>But you must accept</i>
<i>your marriage has been made in God's eyes</i>

46:43.501 --> 46:45.403
<i>and the law's,</i>

46:45.436 --> 46:48.039
<i>and you shame yourself</i>
<i>in trying to revoke it.</i>

46:49.107 --> 46:51.042
<i>Make your peace with Angus.</i>

46:52.544 --> 46:54.345
<i>Be a good wife to him.</i>

46:54.379 --> 46:56.381
[sighs]

46:58.583 --> 47:02.453
Rosa... she was well?

47:02.487 --> 47:03.888
And happy?

47:05.390 --> 47:07.392
Did you speak to her?

47:09.227 --> 47:10.395
I did.

47:13.064 --> 47:16.067
♪ ♪

47:22.540 --> 47:26.945
Mary, I want to talk to you
about the shouting...

47:28.079 --> 47:30.915
...and the people who were hurt
out in the streets.

47:31.950 --> 47:35.253
I know you must have been afraid,
but you were very brave.

47:45.563 --> 47:50.068
Perhaps tomorrow we could walk together.

47:50.101 --> 47:52.036
Out in the gardens?

47:52.070 --> 47:54.105
The bad men will be hanged.

47:55.406 --> 47:56.441
What?

47:57.976 --> 48:00.945
My father cuts their heads off.

48:08.186 --> 48:11.356
[More] "John Wright,
inciting violence on the street.

48:11.389 --> 48:13.558
"Richard Fletcher, inciting to riot.

48:13.591 --> 48:16.394
"Henry Swift,
assaulting the king's soldiers.

48:16.427 --> 48:18.463
Mark Littleton, destroying"--

48:20.965 --> 48:23.468
Henry, I must speak with you about Mary.

48:25.970 --> 48:27.939
[More]
"Destroying a wool merchant's property.

48:27.972 --> 48:30.408
"John Lincoln,
assaulting the king's soldiers,

48:30.441 --> 48:31.609
inciting violence."

48:31.643 --> 48:35.513
These are the ring leaders
that my men apprehended, Your Grace.

48:35.546 --> 48:38.049
[Wolsey]
They rose against the king's peace.

48:38.082 --> 48:40.118
They are rebels. They must pay.

48:44.489 --> 48:46.524
Henry, you must show them mercy.

48:49.327 --> 48:51.162
They are your subjects.

48:53.331 --> 48:54.699
They did not rise up against you.

48:54.932 --> 48:56.234
They are simply hungry
and can find no work.

48:56.267 --> 48:59.137
-You saw the chaos in the streets.
-Yeah.

48:59.170 --> 49:01.572
And London's children all saw bloodshed.

49:03.508 --> 49:04.676
Mary among them.

49:05.710 --> 49:07.512
She is disturbed by it.

49:09.113 --> 49:10.348
Please...

49:14.352 --> 49:17.155
...spare them from further pain.

49:19.023 --> 49:20.692
Save their innocence.

49:22.293 --> 49:25.163
Do not have their fathers' blood
on your hands.

49:32.203 --> 49:33.438
They will hang.

49:35.039 --> 49:36.708
Wolsey, make arrangements.

49:39.544 --> 49:42.313
I serve the king's wish.

49:42.347 --> 49:45.350
♪ ♪

49:45.383 --> 49:47.452
[Meg]
<i>"Be a good wife.</i>

49:47.485 --> 49:49.454
Make your peace."

49:56.227 --> 49:58.062
We have no horses.

49:58.096 --> 50:00.198
He has taken them.

50:00.231 --> 50:01.566
So we will walk.

50:03.401 --> 50:06.404
♪ ♪

50:13.578 --> 50:17.248
[bell tolls, bird caws]

50:17.281 --> 50:20.151
[Oviedo] Your Grace, these men
do not deserve to die.

50:20.184 --> 50:23.554
They are starving. They have nothing.

50:23.588 --> 50:25.556
The worst assaults came
from the royal soldiers.

50:25.590 --> 50:29.060
I have tried, but I will try again.

50:31.462 --> 50:33.598
-[Catherine exhales shakily]
-Your Grace?

50:36.300 --> 50:39.070
[Catherine sighs]

50:39.103 --> 50:42.106
[choir singing]

50:42.140 --> 50:45.143
♪ ♪

50:54.051 --> 50:55.653
Henry, please.

50:55.686 --> 50:57.822
I beg you to reconsider.

50:58.055 --> 50:59.657
I've said I will not.

50:59.690 --> 51:02.693
♪ ♪

51:02.727 --> 51:06.264
The condemned have been found guilty
of attacks on foreign persons

51:06.297 --> 51:08.132
and breaking the king's peace.

51:09.634 --> 51:12.136
Do you have any final words?

51:12.170 --> 51:15.206
-Mercy, please.
-Have mercy.

51:15.239 --> 51:17.141
[man]
Mercy, my Lord!

51:18.676 --> 51:19.811
Hang them.

51:21.212 --> 51:23.748
-Henry--
-They can die without me watching them.

51:23.781 --> 51:26.784
♪ ♪

51:32.256 --> 51:33.658
[Catherine]

51:34.659 --> 51:35.827
Henry.

51:37.829 --> 51:40.097
Henry, I beg you to reconsider.

51:41.332 --> 51:43.301
What they did was wrong,
but they were starving.

51:43.334 --> 51:45.803
They will bend to my will,
and so will you.

51:45.837 --> 51:49.340
The whole of England bows
to your will, Your Grace.

51:52.243 --> 51:54.679
Catherine, go to Mary
and tell her she will be queen.

51:55.813 --> 51:59.350
Queen of Spain, as her grandmother was.

52:00.852 --> 52:02.854
You will marry her to Charles?

52:05.790 --> 52:08.192
Thank you, Henry.

52:09.360 --> 52:11.429
Thank you for our daughter's sake.

52:13.631 --> 52:16.367
And let me never hear the title
"Alter Rex" again.

52:17.535 --> 52:19.837
Your Grace, I beg forgiveness--

52:19.871 --> 52:21.706
My title is Your Majesty.

52:21.739 --> 52:22.874
Remember it.

52:25.776 --> 52:27.378
Your Majesty...

52:28.713 --> 52:30.448
...please spare these men.

52:31.716 --> 52:33.217
I am...

52:35.219 --> 52:36.921
I am with child again.

52:39.423 --> 52:42.426
Please spare them for his sake.

52:42.460 --> 52:45.396
[gentle music]

52:45.429 --> 52:48.432
♪ ♪

52:50.902 --> 52:53.304
It's one final chance.

52:53.337 --> 52:55.873
♪ ♪

52:57.542 --> 52:59.544
Grant them mercy.

52:59.577 --> 53:02.580
♪ ♪

53:04.715 --> 53:06.250
Thank you.

53:13.824 --> 53:16.627
[More] <i>"John Wright,</i>
<i>inciting violence in the street.</i>

53:16.661 --> 53:19.497
<i>"William Smith,</i>
<i>theft of a merchant's property.</i>

53:19.530 --> 53:21.432
<i>"John Lincoln,</i>
<i>assaulting the king's soldiers,</i>

53:21.465 --> 53:22.867
<i>"inciting violence.</i>

53:22.900 --> 53:24.669
<i>May God have mercy on their souls."</i>

53:24.702 --> 53:26.404
[Catherine]
Stop! Stop!

53:26.437 --> 53:29.674
His Majesty the king has pardoned them.

53:29.707 --> 53:32.710
♪ ♪

53:33.811 --> 53:35.746
They may go free.

53:39.383 --> 53:42.253
-God save the king.
-God save the king!

53:42.286 --> 53:43.721
God save King Henry!

53:43.754 --> 53:45.957
[all]

53:55.466 --> 53:57.702
God save the king!

53:57.735 --> 54:00.738
[dramatic music]

54:00.771 --> 54:03.774
♪ ♪

54:09.313 --> 54:11.782
We went hunting, lady mother.

54:12.883 --> 54:15.953
So you have not missed
your poor mother at all?

54:15.987 --> 54:17.622
Albany arrived this morning.

54:17.655 --> 54:19.624
We were gonna ride down to see you.

54:20.658 --> 54:22.360
Angus is gone.

54:24.328 --> 54:26.731
He has taken everything I own.

54:26.764 --> 54:28.933
Everything that is theirs, too.

54:28.966 --> 54:32.970
And my brother will not help me,
and Catherine bids me to...

54:33.004 --> 54:37.041
"keep the peace" and "be a good wife."

54:37.274 --> 54:38.876
But I will not.

54:38.909 --> 54:40.911
He goes too far this time.

54:40.945 --> 54:42.546
So help me.

54:42.580 --> 54:44.715
I know your family
has connections with the Pope.

54:44.749 --> 54:48.986
Petition him on my behalf.
Put to him my case for an annulment.

54:49.020 --> 54:51.389
I have researched it all in law.

54:51.422 --> 54:52.490
I know I have grounds.

54:52.523 --> 54:55.326
It would be the first time
he's agreed to it.

54:55.359 --> 54:56.694
Your chances are not high.

54:56.727 --> 54:58.996
But make my case to him.

54:59.030 --> 55:01.666
Beseech him...

55:01.699 --> 55:06.404
because I will find a way
to rid myself of that Douglas demon

55:06.437 --> 55:09.573
if it is the last thing I ever do.

55:09.607 --> 55:13.344
And none, including Henry and his queen,

55:13.377 --> 55:14.745
shall stop me.

55:14.779 --> 55:17.782
♪ ♪

55:22.620 --> 55:25.523
[man singing dramatically in Latin]

55:25.556 --> 55:28.559
♪ ♪

55:39.336 --> 55:42.339
[dramatic singing in Spanish]

55:42.373 --> 55:45.376
♪ ♪
